        <li>Highly experienced or specialized tutors</li>
        <li>Business or exam preparation expertise</li>
        <li>Detailed progress reports</li>
        <li>Priority scheduling</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Hidden fees and extra costs to watch for</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">When comparing platforms, look beyond the base lesson price. Some costs are not obvious at first glance.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Platform service fees.</strong> Some platforms charge a percentage on top of tutor rates. If a tutor charges $20 per hour and the platform takes 20 percent, you pay $24. Always check what the total cost will be.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Currency conversion fees.</strong> If you are paying in a different currency, your bank or payment processor may charge conversion fees. These small amounts add up over time.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Package expiration.</strong> Some platforms set expiration dates on lesson packages. If you buy 20 lessons but only use 15 before the deadline, you lose the remaining five.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Setup or subscription fees.</strong> A few platforms charge monthly membership fees separate from your lesson costs. Make sure you understand all recurring charges before signing up.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How to find affordable English tutors without sacrificing quality</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">You do not need to spend a lot of money to improve your English. Here are practical tips for getting good lessons at lower prices.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Start with newer tutors.</strong> Many talented tutors are just building their student base. They often charge lower prices while providing excellent lessons. As you find tutors you like, you can stick with them as their prices increase.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Book trial lessons.</strong> Most platforms offer discounted or free trial lessons. Use these to find a tutor whose teaching style fits your needs before committing to regular sessions.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Buy in bulk during sales.</strong> Many platforms run holiday sales or first-time buyer discounts. Stock up on lesson packages during these promotions to save money.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Mix and match.</strong> Combine cheap practice sessions with occasional premium lessons. Use budget tutors for regular conversation practice, and save premium tutors for specific skills like business English or exam prep.</p>

